# Copy this to ".env" in the project root. dispatcher.sh sources it every tick.
# This keeps you on your Claude SUBSCRIPTION (not API billing).

# 1) Generate a long-lived subscription token (uses your Pro/Max plan, NOT the API):
#       claude setup-token
#    Paste the resulting token here:
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat01-REPLACE_ME

# 2) cron uses a minimal PATH. Add wherever `claude` and `jq` live.
#    Find them with:  which claude ; which jq
#    Common spots: Homebrew on Apple Silicon = /opt/homebrew/bin, Intel = /usr/local/bin
PATH=/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin

# 3) (Optional) GitHub edge — only needed if github.enabled is true in schedule.json.
#    Easiest is to run `gh auth login` once interactively. For pure unattended cron,
#    set a token here instead:
GH_TOKEN=ghp_REPLACE_ME_OR_USE_gh_auth_login
